<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued August 07 at 3:00AM CDT until August 07 at 4:00AM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 400 AM CDT
FOR BEAVER AND NORTHEASTERN LIPSCOMB COUNTIES...
At 259 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles east of
Floris, or 6 miles northwest of Beaver, moving southeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Beaver, Forgan, Follett, Gate, Knowles, Elmwood, Mocane, Slapout and
Floris.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
